const faqs = [
  { q: "Who owns Fagor Industrial? Didn't Fagor go bankrupt?", a: "Critical disambiguation — Fagor is two different companies that share the name. Fagor Electrodomésticos (the Spanish residential appliance company that made home refrigerators, dishwashers, washing machines for the Spanish and European consumer market) went bankrupt in 2013 and was subsequently acquired by Brandt, a French appliance company. That Fagor is not what we service. Fagor Industrial — the commercial + industrial equipment company serving restaurants, commercial laundry, and industrial food-service operations — survived the 2013 crisis independently and continues operating as a division of Onnera Group, based in Oñati in the Basque Country of Spain. Onnera Group is part of the Mondragón Cooperative heritage — the largest worker-owned cooperative in the world. Fagor Industrial is what we service for commercial laundry + commercial dishwasher work; the Fagor Industrial brand is independent of the bankrupt Fagor Electrodomésticos residential line." },
  { q: "Fagor commercial laundry models — what does the LA / LR / LN naming mean?", a: "Fagor Industrial's commercial laundry naming convention is straightforward once you know it. LA-series = washers (LA-14, LA-25, LA-35, LA-60, LA-90, LA-110, LA-180 capacity tiers in kilograms, equivalent to roughly 30–400 pounds per load). LR-series = tumble dryers (similar capacity tiers matched to LA washer capacities). LN-series = flatwork ironers (large rotary drum ironers for sheet + tablecloth processing at hotel central laundry + hospital + restaurant linen). LD-series = dry-cleaning machines (less common in LA commercial installations but present at specialty dry-cleaning operators). Our Fagor Industrial service covers the LA-series washer + LR-series dryer lines most commonly; LN ironer and LD dry-clean service is available but less frequent in our LA call volume." },
  { q: "Where in LA do you see Fagor Industrial laundry installed?", a: "Fagor Industrial's LA install base is narrower than Alliance-family or Whirlpool Corp but meaningful in specific niches: Spanish-speaking operator hotels and restaurants where specifying a Spanish brand reflects operator preference or supplier relationship; specific hospital OPL installations where Fagor was specified via the European healthcare equipment consortium channel; LA hotel central laundry at some mid-to-upper hotel properties (less common than Alliance but present at specific independent operators); and restaurant chain central laundry at operations with Spanish or European supplier relationships. The Onnera Group parts chain routes through Fagor Industrial USA distribution; LA lead times typically 3–7 days on specialty parts, faster on common wear items through regional distributors." },
  { q: "Do you also service Fagor commercial dishwashers?", a: "Yes — Fagor Industrial's commercial dishwasher line (AD series undercounter, CO series conveyor, FI series flight-type) is covered at <a href=\"/brands/fagor-dishwasher-repair/\">our Fagor commercial dishwasher page</a>. Both the dishwasher and laundry lines are the same Fagor Industrial brand under the same Onnera Group parent. For operations running a mixed Fagor Industrial kitchen + laundry install — some LA hotels and restaurants pair Fagor dishwashers with Fagor laundry equipment for supplier consolidation — single-call coverage across both lines works through shared Onnera Group parts channel. The dishwasher call falls under the same $120 commercial diagnostic scope." },
  { q: "Mondragón Cooperative — does that affect how the equipment is built?", a: "Mondragón is the worker-owned cooperative federation that originated in Spain's Basque Country in 1956 and grew into the largest cooperative business system in the world. Onnera Group (Fagor Industrial's parent) is a cooperative within that federation. Operationally for the equipment, the cooperative structure means engineering decisions are internally directed by worker-owners rather than being shaped by private equity or conglomerate integration priorities — similar to how Alliance Laundry Systems' ESOP structure affects Speed Queen/UniMac/Huebsch engineering direction. The practical service-side effect: Fagor Industrial parts chains tend to be stable across long model lifecycles, and European engineering conventions (metric fasteners, European electrical standards adapted to North American voltage) show up in the equipment. Our techs keep both metric and standard tooling on the truck for Fagor Industrial service." },
  { q: "What does Fagor Commercial Laundry repair cost in LA?", a: "$120 flat commercial diagnostic, waived with repair. Typical Fagor Industrial service ranges: pressure switch $220–$380, water-inlet valve $240–$400, door gasket (larger capacity) $260–$440, drive belt $240–$400, LR dryer ignitor + flame sensor $260–$440, LR gas valve $320–$520, chemistry-pump integration service $300–$500, LA-series door lock + interlock $280–$460, main motor service $420–$720, bearing service (larger capacity) $520–$880, control board / PLC $700–$1,300, variable-frequency drive $900–$1,500. Most Fagor Industrial calls land $380–$780 parts-and-labor. Capacity scaling affects pricing — LA-180 (400-lb) service runs higher than LA-25 (55-lb) across comparable components. See our <a href=\"/price-list/commercial-dryer-repair-cost/\">commercial dryer repair cost guide</a>." }
];

